summary: Being married off to another lord instead of Jon would Include
body:
Being married off to another lord instead of Jon would Include

• Jon struggling deeply with this choice finding that everythin he’s ever wanted has been taken from him


• Him begging Ned to reconsider this knowing that he might only be a Bastard but he wants you


• Ned trying to fix thingns but failing


• Jon riding out to your house and speaking directly with your father only to be turned away


• You crying and telling Jon that you wanted to be married to him and not this lord


• Jon promising you that he’ll make it right and that he’ll never stop loving you


• Crying the day he goes to the wall


• Crying the day he shows up at your doorstep with an army demanding for your hand

summary: I've seen many people complain about Jon's name being Aegon and saying he should've been named after Visenya. But it kind of...
question: I've seen many people complain about Jon's name being Aegon and saying he should've been named after Visenya. But it kind of makes sense for him to be called Aegon considering how obsessed Rhaegar was with fullfilling the prophecy. With the annulment it was like he said his kids with Elia didn't count. He probably wanted to start over and have kids that met the requirements of the prince who was promised. I wonder if its going to be the same in the books. What do you think?
answer:
part 2: Also I know many people wanted Jon to be called Jaehaerys which would be a good option.

I like Jaehaerys and Aemon personally but I love all the Targaryen names. As far as Aegon, it does make sense that Rhaegar, given his obsession with TPTWP prophecy would name him Aegon. It’s weird because this was never mentioned in the show at all but it is what it is. In regards to the books, I have a feeling it could be different but I’m not so sure. We already have Faegon running around out there too. Lol, talking about ‘the books’….as if we’ll ever get another one xD
